fields.title: Surround yourself with good people and the world will be a little easier
fields.content: Online abuse continues to exist and despite the new measures to combat trolls and hate raids we must continue and keep our communities and group of friends close - like She Codes Brisbane cohorts across all years.

fields.title: Nostalgia can be a blessing or a curse
fields.content: Django envokes feelings and memories of HTML & CSS, on one hand a feeling of excitment to showcase your style and then a back flash of long hours spent applying various css techniques.

fields.title: Unmissable Django Project Deployment.
fields.content: What a great class and a nice sign off to our Django Project althought Heroku was not being co-operative to all of She Codes Brisbane Co-hort its still a nice sign off to Module 3 for 2021.

fields.title: Outrageous Pricing for Parking in Brisbane City
fields.content: If you don't know, now you know! All day parking for $15 on Saturdays which is conveniently located across from the The Hub.

fields.title: Brisbane She Codes Students are back in person
fields.content: Happy students elated after a long awaited return to The Hub, Adeliade Street, Brisbane on Saturday 28th August.
